      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who does the work</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A Certified ProAdvisor rebuilds the file and coordinates with your CPA.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>A complex cleanup is reconstruction, not touch-up. The work is rebuilding damaged or missing periods, re-establishing opening balances that actually reconcile, untangling opening-balance-equity and retained-earnings, consolidating related entities, and re-running reconciliation year by year until every period ties to the bank and to the prior year&rsquo;s close. A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor with active Online and Desktop certifications does that against a written, phased scope, and verifies the file is CPA-ready before handing it over. Where prior years are involved, we coordinate directly with your CPA on prior-period exposure &mdash; but we do not file or amend returns; that is your CPA&rsquo;s work, and we keep that line clean. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support.</p>
